Desc: Generates an energy shield that deals 7% Physical DMG to the attackers. Lasts 3s. 16s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Backfire III</size></color>
Desc: Generates an energy shield that deals 10% Physical DMG to the attackers. Lasts 3s. 16s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Vision Interference</size></color>
Desc: Enemies throw smoke bombs at the target, significantly blocking its vision for 2s. 20s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Vision Interference</size></color>
Desc: Enemies throw smoke bombs at the target, significantly blocking its vision for 4s. 20s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Vision Interference</size></color>
Desc: Enemies throw smoke bombs at the target, significantly blocking its vision for 6s. 20s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Smoke Mine I</size></color>
Desc: Enemies deploy smoke mines to significantly block the vision of the target that triggers them for 2s. 30s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Smoke Mine II</size></color>
Desc: Enemies deploy smoke mines to significantly block the vision of the target that triggers them for 4s. 30s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Smoke Mine III</size></color>
Desc: Enemies deploy smoke mines to significantly block the vision of the target that triggers them for 6s. 30s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Combustion Mine I</size></color>
Desc: Enemies deploy a Combustion Mine creating a burning area once triggered. Units stay inside this area for 1.5s will be burned for 2s, taking damage once every second. At the end of this duration, an explosion will interrupt the affected unit's action. CD: 15s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Defense Order I</size></color>
Desc: Enemies summon 3 Corrupted of low strength and take 80% less damage when these Corrupted are alive. 30s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Defense Order II</size></color>
Desc: Enemies summon 3 Corrupted of medium strength and take 80% less damage when these Corrupted are alive. 30s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Defense Order III</size></color>
Desc: Enemies summon 3 Corrupted of high strength and take 80% less damage when these Corrupted are alive. 30s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Disconnected Link I</size></color>
Desc: Every enemy attack applies one Mark of Disconnection on the target. Once the number of Marks reaches 5, the affected target will be stunned for 1s. 8s cooldown between each stun.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Disconnected Link II</size></color>
Desc: Every enemy attack applies one Mark of Disconnection on the target. Once the number of Marks reaches 3, the affected target will be stunned for 1s. 8s cooldown between each stun.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Temperature Disorder</size></color>
Desc: After taking Fire DMG, enemies will take 45% more Ice DMG for 8s. 8s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Stance Switch</size></color>
Desc: 15s after the battle starts, enemies will gain high Damage Reduction for 20s, then become Frail, taking a lot more damage for 15s. (The Damage Reduction bonus and Frail status will keep rotating)

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Shadow</size></color>
Desc: Enemy attacks have a 15% chance to inflict Corruption"" on the target for 5s. This effect cannot be stacked and has an 8s cooldown on the same unit.""

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Beacon</size></color>
Desc: There will be an increased amount of enemies.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Thunderclap</size></color>
Desc: Enemy attacks have a 10% chance to deal bonus 10% Lightning DMG and "Electrocute" their target for 1.5s. Electrocuted units will be struck by lightning every 1.5s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Thunderclap</size></color>
Desc: Enemy attacks have a 15% chance to deal bonus 15% Lightning DMG and "Electrocute" their target for 3s. Electrocuted units will be struck by lightning every 1.5s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Thunderclap</size></color>
Desc: Enemy attacks have a 20% chance to deal bonus 20% Lightning DMG and "Electrocute" their target for 4.5s. Electrocuted units will be struck by lightning every 1.5s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Bloodlust</size></color>
Desc: Enemies gain 15% more damage for every 20% HP lost.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Dark</size></color>
Desc: Enemy attacks have a 10% chance to deal bonus 10% Dark DMG and stun their target for 1s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Dark</size></color>
Desc: Enemy attacks have a 15% chance to deal bonus 15% Dark DMG and stun their target for 1s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Dark</size></color>
Desc: Enemy attacks have a 20% chance to deal bonus 20% Dark DMG and stun their target for 1s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Freeze</size></color>
Desc: Enemy attacks have a 10% chance to deal bonus 10% Ice DMG and freeze their target for 1s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Freeze</size></color>
Desc: Enemy attacks have a 15% chance to deal bonus 15% Ice DMG and freeze their target for 1s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Freeze</size></color>
Desc: Enemy attacks have a 20% chance to deal bonus 20% Ice DMG and freeze their target for 1s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Energy Absorb</size></color>
Desc: Attacking enemies will restore your HP by 20%. 5s cooldown.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Last Stand</size></color>
Desc: Enemies with HP below 50% will deal more damage but also take more damage.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Constant Vigilance</size></color>
Desc: Riot is dormant and fires laser beams intermittently at the beginning. It will wake up gradually when more and more minions are defeated.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Naughty White Shark</size></color>
Desc: After Shark-speare enters Phase 2, Phase 1 Shark-speare will appear to mess you up intermittently.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Last Stand</size></color>
Desc: The more HP Roland loses, the more powerful he will become.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Soldier Strike</size></color>
Desc: A wraith soldier will appear and charge you intermittently.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Elemental Resistance</size></color>
Desc: Elemental Resistance [H]: When the enemy receives Elemental DMG of the same type more than 33% of max HP, it gains a corresponding Elemental Resistance (only 1 resistance at a time).
TeachingContents: text: No additional information

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Cruciata Arrival</size></color>
Desc: Cruciata Arrival: When Amberia's HP drops to 60%, 35%, and 10%, she will conjure a Grave Mark that nullifies all DMG dealt to her. Amberia will perform a fierce attack 20s after the Grave Mark exists on field.
TeachingContents: text: No additional information

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Nightmare</size></color>
Desc: 2 wraith soldiers will appear to charge you. The charging interval is reduced to 10s from the 2nd charging onward.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Undying</size></color>
Desc: All enemies other than Qu will revive in 25s after they die.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Cross Inverter</size></color>
Desc: Amberia will perform a fierce attack 15s after the Grave Mark exists on field.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Stage 3 Environment</size></color>
Desc: Enemies will give bonus effects to Qu when they are on field.
TeachingContents: text: No additional information

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Dead Zone</size></color>
Desc: Recommended Uniframe
TeachingContents: text: No additional information

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Battle Cry</size></color>
Desc: Every 20s, the enemy will unleash Battle Cry to knock the player back (can be interrupted by stun skills).

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Gravitational Pull</size></color>
Desc: A gravity circle appears under the character every 20s. Characters inside the circle will be pulled toward its center, and lose 50 Dodge Gauge every 0.5s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Elemental Resonance</size></color>
Desc: Elemental Resonance: Elemental ATK will add monster an Elemental Mark. Two different Elemental Marks will make Resonance, adding Vulnerability to BOSS and killing little monsters

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Local Burn</size></color>
Desc: Local Burn: Burn Zones occur on the field somewhere, when characters or enemies are burned by fire, they will receive Vulnerability. Fire Burning will make the enemy's E-Shield invalid for 15s

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Ascnet</size></color>
Desc: Ascnet: Start chanting when Luna's HP is 85%, 50% and 15%. While chanting, summons unknown Constructs to assist in battle. Unknown Constructs will leave for a while if they are Stunned or fatally injured

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Ascendant Arrival</size></color>
Desc: With the improvement of Overload Level, Unknown Constructs will support in battles more frequently, and will stay in field when Luna's HP is 15%

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Chomper</size></color>
Desc: Chomper: One Chomper will grow up in the field every other 5 s starting from the 5th second. Each Chomper comes with an Elemental Mark, and will reborn after 15s of death. The max number of Chomper is 4 by default, up to 6 in Overload III / IV and 8 in Overload V

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Hetero-Resonance</size></color>
Desc: In the field, the effect that Chomper added to all monsters upgrades to Level 3, and the Chomper will no longer carry Element Mark when it is born

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Reborn</size></color>
Desc: Pterygota Queen Wings will auto recover 60s later after being damaged

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>E-Screen Defense</size></color>
Desc: E-Screen Defense: The enemies have a large Damage Resistance Shield, which will be temporarily invalid for 15s after burning by fire in the scene

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>E-Screen Overload</size></color>
Desc: Greatly increases Damage Resistance of Monster's E-Screen Defense

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Hetero-Radiation</size></color>
Desc: Hetero-Radiation: When there are 2 Chompers, all monsters will be added a Lv.1 Black Hole; 4 Chompers, added a Lv.1 Radiation; 6 Chompers, added a Lv.1 Strike; and 8 Chompers, added a Lv.1 Recovery

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Infect</size></color>
Desc: Infect: Siren will leave an infection area on the field for every 25s. Units in contact with it will be <color=#CF0000>infected for 5s</color> (Constructs will lose additional HP).

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Familiar</size></color>
Desc: Familiar: Siren has 6 familiars that give it <color=#CF0000>DMG Immunity</color>. Siren summons 2 and <color=#CF0000>randomly marks 1</color> (unmarked familiars cannot be locked) at the start of the battle. Marked familiars will be <color=#CF0000>devoured, respawned, and randomly marked again</color> until 6 have been devoured. Familiars will <color=#CF0000>revive and weaken you</color> after you destroy them.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Burning Mark</size></color>
Desc: Burning Mark: The familiar is <color=#CF0000>burning</color>. When devoured by Siren, <color=#34aff9>its infection will rebuff against Siren</color> and your HP will be restored. Otherwise, Siren will <color=#CF0000>devour it and leave an infection area</color> that continuously infects nearby enemies and drains their HP.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Rising Tide</size></color>
Desc: Siren will continuously restore its HP in the infection area.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Awaken</size></color>
Desc: Marked familiars gain an additional power: Burning Mark (attacks have a chance to Burn enemies). Stealth Mark (attacks have a chance to Freeze enemies).

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Stealth Mark</size></color>
Desc: Stealth Mark: The familiar is <color=#CF0000>stealthy</color>. When its HP is more than 60%, it will head to an infection area. When devoured by Siren, <color=#34aff9>if it is not infected, it will rebuff against Siren</color> and your power will be boosted. Otherwise, Siren will <color=#CF0000>devour it, leave an infection area</color>, and summon Buthus that will give Siren great DMG Immunity.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Dirge</size></color>
Desc: Dirge: Siren will become paralyzed and Vulnerable for 5s after devouring 6 familiars. Each <color=#34aff9>rebuff will increase the duration by 1s and cleanse 1 infection area</color>. If all familiars are devoured, cleanse <color=#34aff9>all</color> infection areas. After that, DMG dealt by Siren will increase based on <color=#CF0000>the number of familiars devoured successfully</color>.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Four Signs</size></color>
Desc: Four Signs: Rosetta will <color=#CF0000>change the weather for every 25% HP lost</color> (Thunderstorm will occur with only 25% HP left) and summon soldiers with <color=#CF0000>the corresponding resistance</color>. <color=#CF0000>The current weather will be growing extreme over time.</color>

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Buoy</size></color>
Desc: Buoy: There are 3 buoys on the field. After destroying the soldier corresponding to the current weather, the buoys will restore the weather and <color=#CF0000>activate 1 buoy that absorbs the corresponding Element</color>, reducing Rosetta's all Elemental Resistance <color=#CF0000>before the weather changes again</color>. <color=#CF0000>After the weather changes</color>, inactivated buoys will disappear.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Nature Poetry</size></color>
Desc: Nature Poetry: Activating 3 buoys when Thunderstorm is in effect will trigger the following bonuses: <color=#34aff9>3 different Elements</color> will reduce Rosetta's all Elemental Resistance; <color=#34aff9>2 same Elements</color> will grant you DMG reduction; <color=#34aff9>3 same Elements</color> will continuously restore your HP.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Apocalypse</size></color>
Desc: The extreme weather will strengthen Thunderstorm. More lightning strikes will hit with higher frequency.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Obsession</size></color>
Desc: Activating a buoy will not reduce Rosetta's Resistance against the activated Element.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Parasitize</size></color>
Desc: Parasitize: Surfer is parasitized by the <color=#CF0000>Parasite (Red Effect)</color> at the start of battle. The Parasite will drain its host's life every second and spawn a Corrupted every 25s. After that, the Parasite will <color=#CF0000>detach from its host and attach to you or the nearest Surfer.</color>

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Evolve</size></color>
Desc: Evolve: If the Parasite has <color=#CF0000>spawned 3 times</color>, the Corrupted spawned after that will be more powerful.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Tarnish</size></color>
Desc: Tarnish: Surfer gains <color=#CF0000>great DMG reduction</color>. <color=#CF0000>It will keep decreasing after the Parasite is removed.</color>

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Antibody</size></color>
Desc: Antibody: Destroying the spawned Corrupted will grant you <color=#34aff9>an antibody</color> for 10s and <color=#34aff9>remove your Parasite (if parasitized)</color>, during which you are immune to Parasitize, and <color=#34aff9>attacking a host with 2 different types of Signal Orbs</color> will prevent the Parasite from evolving (ineffective against the evolved Parasite).

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Constrict</size></color>
Desc: Unable to switch members when being parasitized.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>The Land of Blood Thirst</size></color>
Desc: The Grizzly members will no longer recover their HP.

Name: <color=#CF0000>Two Sharks One Heart<size=34></size></color>
Desc: The second Shark-speare will appear immediately after the first Shark-speare.

Name: Sublimate
Desc: 2 Sanctuary Guards will <color=#34aff9>accumulate energy</color>.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Energy Accumulation:</color> Gains 2 energy per second and DMG dealt (up to 80 energy).

Name: Fusion
Desc: When the energy reaches its maximum, merges into <color=#34aff9>Twilight State</color> and continuously <color=#34aff9>consumes energy</color>. When dealing DMG, gains <color=#CF0000>1 stack of Decree</color>.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Twilight State:</color> When attacking, gains a shield and reduces the enemy's speed. Creates Energy Storm to deal DMG to enemies for every 20 energy consumed.
text: <color=#34aff9>Energy Consumption</color>: Consumes 2 energy per second while in Twilight/Bishop State.

Name: Leader
Desc: When reaching <color=#CF0000>8 stacks of Decrees</color>, materializes into <color=#34aff9>Bishop State</color> and regains 60 energy and 30% of max HP.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Bishop State:</color> Inherits Energy Storm and performs cluster strike. Attacks will restore HP.

Name: Legacy
Desc: When exiting a fusion state, Sanctuary Guard will <color=#34aff9>recover HP</color> based on the remaining HP in that state.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Health Recovery:</color> Recovers HP equal to 40% of the remaining HP in the fusion state. For instance, Sanctuary Guard will recover 20 HP if it has 50 HP when exiting the fusion state.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Linking Oath</size></color>
Desc: Enemies will heal their allies for 50% of their remaining HP while in the dying state and perform fusion instantly (once only).

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Noble Sacrifice</size></color>
Desc: When an enemy dies, its allies gain a 30% DMG bonus, resistance bonus, and shield.

Name: Phase I - Judgement
Desc: Machiavelli will summon 2 <color=#34aff9>Iron Thorns</color> for every 25% HP lost. The Iron Thorns will destroy the platform in 35s.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Iron Thorn:</color>
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightTieji.png

Name: Agent of Willpower
Desc: Machiavelli will create a <color=#34aff9>Mirror Image</color> to protect Iron Thorns while in the Judgement phase.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Mirror Image:</color> Randomly summons a Mirror Image - Violence/Law. The Mirror Image cannot be locked on or destroyed.
text: <color=#34aff9>Mirror Image - Violence:</color> When dealing DMG, reduces the duration of the Judgement phase by 1s and has a chance to Burn the enemy for 4s.
text: <color=#34aff9>Mirror Image - Law-:</color> When dealing DMG, reduces the enemy's speed for 4s and has a chance to imprison them for 2s.

Name: Phase II - Purge
Desc: After being defeated, Machiavelli will revive and create a Mirror Shard for every 15s. The Mirror Image will imitate Machiavelli's attack pattern.
TeachingContents: text: No additional information

Name: Cognitive Overload
Desc: When there are 3 shards, 1 of them will turn into an <color=#34aff9>Enhanced Mirror Image</color>. The more shards/Mirror Images exist, the weaker Machiavelli will be.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Enhanced Mirror Image:</color> Randomly summons up to 2 Enhanced Mirror Images - Violence/Law. They cannot be locked on or destroyed.
text: <color=#34aff9>Enhanced Mirror Image - Violence:</color> When dealing DMG, restores Machiavelli's HP and has a chance to Burn the enemy for 5s.
text: <color=#34aff9>Enhanced Mirror Image - Law-:</color> When dealing DMG, affects the target's movement for 4s and has a chance to imprison them for 2.5s.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>No Time to Lose I</size></color>
Desc: Reduces the duration of the Judgement phase to 30s.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>No Time to Lose II</size></color>
Desc: Reduces the duration of the Judgement phase to 25s.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>No Time to Lose III</size></color>
Desc: Reduces the duration of the Judgement phase to 20s.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Abyss</size></color>
Desc: Your controlling characters will fall from the collapsed platform.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Soul Ripper</size></color>
Desc: The shards will heal Machiavelli's HP when dealing DMG.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Shackle Breaker</size></color>
Desc: Mirror Images and shards become immune to Matrix.

Name: <color=#2F0000><size=34>Emergency Retreat</size></color>
Desc: Initial Target: Defeat the Corrupted and protect the <color=#34aff9>Grizzly members</color> on the way to the evacuation point.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9> The Grizzly members</color>: All Grizzly members will slowly regain HP and move to the evacuation point instead of joining battle. <color=#34aff9>Their movement speed will greatly increase</color> when allied Constructs are near them. <color=#FF0000>They will be unable to move when their HP drops below 50%</color>.

Name: <color=#2F0000><size=34>Last Barrage</size></color>
Desc: Final Target: <color=#CF0000>Last Barrage</color> will be triggered when all the Grizzly members <color=#34aff9>retreat from battle</color>. Defeat the enemies to win your battle.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Retreat from battle</color>: All the Grizzly members have <color=#34aff9>retreated</color> or <color=#CF0000>died</color>.
text: <color=#FF0000>Last Barrage</color>: A boss wave on a high difficulty level. Defeat the enemies to clear this stage.

Name: <color=#2F0000><size=34>Reinforcing Grizzlies</size></color>
Desc: When Last Barrage is triggered, all retreated Grizzly members will return to battle and expand <color=#34aff9>Support Field</color>. Constructs inside the field will gain bonuses.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Charging Support Field</color>: Gains an additional Signal Orb when dealing/receiving DMG every 5s. The effect disappears 3s after leaving the field. The effect is shown below.
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightblueball.png
text: <color=#34aff9>Defense Support Field</color>: Gains Super Armor. The effect disappears 3s after leaving the field. The effect is shown below.
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightyellowsheild.png
text: <color=#34aff9>Attack Support Field</color>: Deals 30% more DMG. The effect disappears 3s after leaving the field. The effect is shown below.
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightredattack.png
text: <color=#34aff9>Tips</color>: All 3 types of Support Fields can be activated at the same time. Making good use of them will help you turn the tide in battle.
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightronghe.png

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Null Heal</size></color>
Desc: After Voodoo goes into Defensive Mode, characters cannot be healed.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Legacy</size></color>
Desc: The enhancement effects of Voodoo won't be cleared.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Inevitable Choice</size></color>
Desc: In Defensive Mode, when a minion is eliminated, Voodoo will directly absorb another minion.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Radiation</size></color>
Desc: In Defensive Mode, Voodoo deals damage to characters over time.

Name: Defensive Phase
Desc: At <color=#34aff9>85%/60%/30% HP</color>, Voodoo enters <color=#34aff9>Defensive Mode</color> with minions coming from <color=#34aff9>2 Portals</color> that, when within <color=#34aff9>5m</color> of Voodoo, are absorbed by Voodoo. Defensive Mode greatly raises <color=#34aff9>DMG Reduction</color> and clears Evolution effects.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Black</color> always spawn from the Red Portal.
text: <color=#34aff9>White</color> always spawn from the Green Portal.

Name: The First Round of Evolution
Desc: Devour White: Emit poisonous gas continuously within <color=#34aff9>5m</color>. Characters within range take DMG per second. Devour Black: Characters are poisoned and take DMG over time. Being within <color=#34aff9>5m</color> of Voodoo will clear the poison.

Name: The Second Round of Evolution
Desc: Devour White: While in <color=#34aff9>Bird</color> Form, before each attack, Voodoo strikes lightning at the characters on the field. Devour Black: While in <color=#34aff9>Beast</color> Form, before each attack, Voodoo strikes lightning at the characters on the field.

Name: Final Evolution 1
Desc: Devour White: Voodoo creates Dolls. When a Doll has <color=#34aff9>less HP Percentage</color> than the characters on the field, it steals HP from them to heal itself over time. A Doll takes damage <color=#34aff9>periodically</color>.""""

Name: Final Evolution 2
Desc: Devour Black: Every <color=#34aff9>10s</color>, Voodoo creates a doll with an aura close to the character. When being inside the aura for <color=#34aff9>6s</color>, the doll will be wrecked and continuously shoot lightning bolts at the character.
TeachingContents: text:<color=#34aff9>闪电人偶</color>会复制角色外貌出现在玩家身边如下图所示
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightshandian.png

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Power of Horn</size></color>
Desc: While Super Armor is active, Ox gains more Resistance.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Polar Ram</size></color>
Desc: Upon impact, Ox's Dash Attack will drag the player to its destination. When it expires, additionally inflicts a 40% Slow Down for 2.5s.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Reversed Shockwave</size></color>
Desc: All attacks by Ox send shockwaves, and all shockwaves travel back. While Berserk is active, Ox sends even more shockwaves.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>The Mighty Ox!</size></color>
Desc: There are two Oxen on the field at the same time.

Name: Strong Ox
Desc: While Super Armor is active, Ox has more Resistance.

Name: Blinking Mine
Desc: There are <color=#34aff9>Blinking Mines</color> on the field. <color=#34aff9>Matching 3-Pings</color> next to a Mine will activate the Mine.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Blinking Mine</color>: <color=#34aff9>Enemies</color> who are caught within the range of a Blinking Mine will be <color=#34aff9>directly stunned</color> and knocked down.

Name: Dragon Breath Device
Desc: There are <color=#34aff9>Dragon Breath Devices</color> on the field. <color=#34aff9>Matching 3-Pings</color> next to such a device will activate it.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Dragon Breath Device</color>: Summons dragon breaths to attack <color=#34aff9>enemies</color>, significantly <color=#34aff9>reducing their Super Armor</color> and <color=#34aff9>increasing their damage taken</color>.

Name: Strength of Ox
Desc: While <color=#FF0000>Super Armor is active, Ox has significantly more DEF</color>. Also, at less than 60% HP, Ox goes <color=#FF0000>Berserk</color>.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#FF0000>Berserk</color>: Its attacks <color=#FF0000>send shockwaves</color> and it <color=#FF0000>cannot be knocked down</color>. Also, it <color=#FF0000>ignores Matrix</color>, but <color=#34aff9>significantly loses all DEFs.</color>

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Refinement - Crit</size></color>
Desc: Activating any device will grant 30% CRIT Rate to the players within range for 10s.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Refinement - Heal</size></color>
Desc: Activating any device restores 5% HP to nearby allies per second for 10s.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Refinement - CD</size></color>
Desc: When all devices are activated, the cooldown is reduced from 60s to 40s.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Polarized Defense</size></color>
Desc: In its initial form, the Dragon has significantly more Resistance. After turning into the Element Dragon, the Resistance against its associated stat will further increase, but the Resistance against its opposite stat will reduce.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Final Judgment</size></color>
Desc: The Dragon's Ultimate, Final Judgment, deals significantly more damage.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Elemental Corruption</size></color>
Desc: When the Dragon deals stat damage to the player, inflicts special debuffs based on what that stat is.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Berserk Dragon</size></color>
Desc: The Dragon never stops with its endless attacks.

Name: Elemental Drain
Desc: The Dragon starts in its <color=#34aff9>Normal Form</color>, but it keeps absorbing the Elemental DMG dealt by players. At less than 80% HP, it transforms.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Normal Form</color>: The Dragon has <color=#34aff9>higher Physical Resistance</color> but <color=#34aff9>lower Elemental Resistance.</color>

Name: Elemental Incarnate
Desc: When the Dragon transforms, <color=#FF0000>it transforms into the associated Elemental Dragon based on the most Elemental DMG it absorbs in its first phase</color>.
TeachingContents: text: TIPS: If the Dragon <color=#34aff9>doesn't take any Elemental DMG before it transforms</color>, a random Element is chosen.

Name: Elemental Discharge
Desc: Once turned into an Elemental Dragon, Dragon's <color=#FF0000>attacks will inflict additional effects</color>, and different types of Elemental Dragon have <color=#34aff9>different Elemental Resistance</color>. For details, see the description on the right.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#FF0000>Fire Dragon</color>: Attacks by the Dragon inflict <color=#FF0000>Delayed Fire</color>, <color=#FF0000>its Fire Resistance is increased</color>, and its <color=#34aff9>Dark Resistance is reduced</color>. When Elemental Corruption is active, attacks also inflict damage over time.
text:

text: <color=#FF0000>Lightning Dragon</color>: Attacks by the Dragon inflict <color=#FF0000>Additional Lightning</color>, <color=#FF0000>its Lightning Resistance is increased</color>, and its <color=#34aff9>Ice Resistance is reduced</color>. When Elemental Corruption is active, attacks generate Delayed Lightning upon hitting an enemy.
text:

text: <color=#FF0000>Ice Dragon</color>: Attacks by the Dragon inflict <color=#FF0000>Additional Ice Cones</color>, <color=#FF0000>its Ice Resistance is increased</color>, and its <color=#34aff9>Fire Resistance is reduced</color>. When Elemental Corruption is active, attacks slow enemies upon impact.
text:

text: <color=#FF0000>Dark Dragon</color>: Attacks by the Dragon inflict <color=#FF0000>Additional Dark Explosions</color>, <color=#FF0000>its Dark Resistance is increased</color>, and its <color=#34aff9>Lightning Resistance is reduced</color>. When Elemental Corruption is active, attacks reduce an enemy's DEF upon impact.

Name: Final Judgment
Desc: At less than 30% HP, the Dragon casts its Ultimate <color=#FF0000>Final Judgment</color>. Its damage is significantly reduced for every <color=#34aff9>broken arm</color> the Elemental Dragon has.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#FF0000>Final Judgment</color>: Deals massive damage to all characters one time. Then, deals damage to them over time.
text:

text: <color=#34aff9>Break the Arm</color>: Destroying the Dragon's arm will <color=#34aff9>significantly reduce the damage dealt by Final Judgment</color>. Dealing damage associated with the opposite stat can <color=#34aff9>more easily break the Dragon's arm</color>.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Steel Module</size></color>
Desc: All characters have Super Armor permanently.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Shield Module</size></color>
Desc: Every 20s, gains a DMG Immunity Shield. When shattered, the timer restarts.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Spread Module</size></color>
Desc: Upon dealing Elemental DMG, there is a 10% chance to deal the same amount of damage to all parts of the Dragon again.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Stealth Bombardment</size></color>
Desc: Bombardment at the shield absorption stage <color=#34aff9>will not trigger Extreme Dodge</color>.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Energy Refine</size></color>
Desc: At the shield absorption stage, if no Glory Clones exist, <color=#34aff9>summons</color> a Glory Clone with <color=#34aff9>10%</color> HP of the original. Otherwise, sacrifices the Glory Clone to summon a stronger one.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Energy Max</size></color>
Desc: The shield absorption stage increases by <color=#34aff9>4%</color> every second.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Luminous Evolution</size></color>
Desc: When both sets of shields have been absorbed or dropped below 30% HP, enemies will enter <color=#34aff9>Phase II</color>.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Accel Time</size></color>
Desc: Moon Eater's arms charge <color=#34aff9>2%</color> faster every second.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Harden</size></color>
Desc: To cut off the enemy's arm, it requires attacks that are <color=#34aff9>different</color> from the last time. Attack Types: <color=#34aff9>Signal Orb skills, Basic Attack, and Signature</color>

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Assimilate</size></color>
Desc: When the enemy's arm is severed, the enemy's Resistance to <color=#34aff9>that attack's element</color> will increase until the next time its arm is severed.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Wrath</size></color>
Desc: When Moon Eater Phase II is in wrath, it will absorb all blood on the ground. Each puddle of blood <color=#34aff9>decreases all characters'</color> Max HP by <color=#34aff9>10%</color>.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Demon Bane's Might</size></color>
Desc: Demon Bane gains <color=#34aff9>Berserk</color>. Its aggressiveness and ATK become higher.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Heaven Breaker's Guard</size></color>
Desc: Heaven Breaker gains <color=#34aff9>Hesitant</color>. Its Finisher Gauge will recover if it is not attacked for 5s.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>God Slayer's Techniques</size></color>
Desc: God Slayer gains <color=#34aff9>Rigid Body</color>. All DMG received is reduced to 1. This effect is removed when it takes DMG 12 times and will resume in 8s.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Rematch</size></color>
Desc: The first enemy wave becomes MC Solar. When defeated, it will be repaired and call forth Demon Bane, Heaven Breaker, and God Slayer to fight together. Demon Bane, Heaven Breaker, and God Slayer will not attack for 20s after receiving Speed Attack.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Visual Enhancement</size></color>
Desc: Characters' CRIT Rates increase.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Drain Power</size></color>
Desc: Critical hits increase DMG by 5% for 6s. It can be stacked up to 5 times. Its duration resets every time it is triggered.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Lunar Character I</size></color>
Desc: Lunar Enhancement 1

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Lunar Character II</size></color>
Desc: Lunar Enhancement 2

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Flexible Strategy</size></color>
Desc: Dodge Gauge recovers faster.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Heating Up</size></color>
Desc: Characters will be Invincible for 3s upon receiving DMG.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Operation Continues</size></color>
Desc: HP recovers every second for 10s after Speed Attack.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Withstand I</size></color>
Desc: Enemies' Finisher Gauges lose 10% less.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Withstand II</size></color>
Desc: Enemies' Finisher Gauges lose 20% less.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Withstand III</size></color>
Desc: Enemies' Finisher Gauges lose 30% less.

Name: Shield Absorption
Desc: When shields are present on the field, enemies will regularly <color=#34aff9>absorb</color> them. When they absorb a shield, they <color=#34aff9>do not move</color>.
TeachingContents: Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightGuanghui.png

Name: Mechanical Domination
Desc: When the enemy is absorbing a shield, it will control the Shield Generator to <color=#34aff9>fire at the characters</color>.
TeachingContents: Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightGuanghuipaoji.png

Name: Energy Boost
Desc: When the shield absorption rate reaches 100%, the shield will be destroyed. Enemies' <color=#34aff9>Fire and Lightning Resistance</color> increase by <color=#34aff9>30%</color> after absorbing the first set of shields, while their <color=#34aff9>Dark and Ice Resistance</color> increase by <color=#34aff9>30%</color> after absorbing the second set.

Name: Arm Augmentation
Desc: Moon Eater charges its arms continuously. When they are charged to <color=#34aff9>100%</color>, its attacks will inflict <color=#34aff9>additional effects</color>. Severing its arms will <color=#34aff9>empty the charge progress</color>.
TeachingContents: Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightYizhonggongjifudai.png

Name: Dynamic Calibration
Desc: Moon Eater Phase I has the <color=#34aff9>"Dynamic Calibration"</color> effect that will continuously restore its HP. This effect is removed when its leg is severed for the first time.

Name: Resect
Desc: When Moon Eater's Super Armor is <color=#34aff9>emptied</color> in Phase I, receiving attacks again will <color=#34aff9>reset</color> Matrix cooldown and launch a counterattack. Dodging this counterattack with Matrix and <color=#34aff9>attacking it again</color> before Matrix ends will sever its limb.
TeachingContents: Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightDuanjiao.png

text: After emptying Super Armor, <color=#34aff9>front attacks</color> will lure the enemy into using a counterattack that can have its <color=#34aff9>arm</color> severed, while <color=#34aff9>back attacks</color> will lure it into using a counterattack that can have its <color=#34aff9>leg</color> severed.

Name: Residuals
Desc: The enemy will leave corrosive blood in place when its limb is severed, dealing continuous <color=#34aff9>DMG</color> to characters in contact with it.
TeachingContents: Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightXueye.png

Name: Four Great Powers
Desc: God Slayer, Demon Bane, Heaven Breaker, and MC Solar will appear one after the other. Defeat them all to clear this stage.
TeachingContents: Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightRitian.png

Name: Decision
Desc: After Moon Eater's Super Armor is emptied in Phase I, <color=#34aff9>front attacks</color> will lure the enemy into using a counterattack that can have its <color=#34aff9>arm</color> severed, while <color=#34aff9>back attacks</color> will lure it into using a counterattack that can have its <color=#34aff9>leg</color> severed.
TeachingContents: text: After emptying Super Armor, <color=#34aff9>front attacks</color> will lure the enemy into using a counterattack that can have its <color=#34aff9>arm</color> severed, while <color=#34aff9>back attacks</color> will lure it into using a counterattack that can have its <color=#34aff9>leg</color> severed.

Name: Evolution
Desc: When Moon Eater's Super Armor is emptied in Phase II, attacking it in Matrix will sever its arm. Only 1 arm can be severed at a time.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Infection Spreading</size></color>
Desc: The Corrupted will explode after being defeated.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Elimination of Anomalies</size></color>
Desc: There will also be a "Data" Jaspers at the beginning of the battle, who will attack your team as well.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Burning Method</size></color>
Desc: Jaspers gains "Radiation". His attacks will make Constructs Burn and lose HP over a certain period.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Beyond Evolution</size></color>
Desc: Jaspers will not be affected by the Matrix. When Jaspers' HP drops below 50%, another Jaspers will appear and attack your team.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Bravery</size></color>
Desc: Gain 2 sets of Signal Orbs after performing a Uniframe's Finishing Move.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Power Capture</size></color>
Desc: Character deals more Extra DMG and becomes Invincible for 10s after performing the Uniframe's Finishing Move.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Life Drain</size></color>
Desc: Character restore 15% of Max HP after performing the Uniframe's Finishing Move.

Name: Data Collection
Desc: There will be <color=#34aff9>five Corrupted</color> in the battlefield at the beginning of the battle. Jaspers will collect their battle experiment data in the background and enter the battlefield as an evolved version before the countdown ends.
TeachingContents: text: Uniframes' <color=#34aff9>Finishing Move</color> can stop Jaspers' evolution.

Name: Evolution Complete
Desc: Jaspers enters the battlefield and gains buffs based on <color=#FF0000>the number of Corrupted who survived the Uniframe's Finishing Move</color>. There will also be other Corrupted to assist him.
TeachingContents: text: TIPS: The Corrupted who enter the battlefield with Jaspers will provide buffs to him and will immediately revive after being knocked down.

Name: Sample Leakage
Desc: After Jaspers' HP drops below a certain level, <color=#FF0000>two extra Corrupted will join the battle</color> and provide buffs for him.
TeachingContents: text: Attack Jaspers first. And the victory is yours once Jaspers is down.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Magic Boost</size></color>
Desc: Lv.1 minions will be enhanced by the witch and gain DMG Reduction.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Sea</size></color>
Desc: The sea needs more sacrifices. All enemies lose 50% Sacrifice Points.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Magic Distribution</size></color>
Desc: After eating the Delicious Mermaid, the witch will get poisoned and summon 2 invincible enemies with her last magic.

Name: Witch Power
Desc: The witch possesses powerful magic and takes <color=#34aff9>significantly less damage</color>.

Name: Delicious Mermaid
Desc: All enemies killed will be eaten by the sea. When the Sacrifice Points reach 100%, the sea will summon the Delicious Mermaid. The witch will eat it, lose all her Witch Power, and <color=#34aff9>become Vulnerable</color>.
TeachingContents: Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightmeiweirenyu.png

Name: FArmor
Desc: Only high Crit frames can break through its armor. (Gains increased DMG Reduction from Tank Omniframes)

Name: FRes-
Desc: The external tubing has stored a lot of organic composite pigments. Highly flammable and prone to explode. (Reduces Fire Resistance.)

Name: IRes+
Desc: Its body is made with a special metal for storing new types of pigments. Performs well in low temperatures and not easily corroded. (Increases Ice Resistance.)

Name: PRes-
Desc: An old model made with old experimental frame materials. Its tenacity and attack resistance are average. (Reduces Physical Resistance.)

Name: DRes+
Desc: A machine deeply corrupted by the Punishing Virus. It has high dark energy resistance. (Increases Dark Resistance.)

Name: Astraphobia
Desc: Vassago, a mechanoid serpent that strikes with precision and conceals itself in the sand by using strong electric currents. (Reduces Lightning Resistance.)

Name: FRes+
Desc: Vassago hides in the sand, away from all that is flammable. (Increases Fire Resistance.)

Name: IRes-
Desc: An AI mechanoid designed to imitate humans, its low cold resistance is its weakness. (Reduces Ice Resistance.)

Name: LRes+
Desc: An AI mechanoid designed to imitate humans, its high level bioelectric signal simulation makes it resistant to electric threats. (Increases Lightning Resistance.)

Name: DRes-
Desc: The damage on its Inver-Device renders its consciousness unstable and prone to corruption. (Reduces Dark Resistance.)

Name: Pres+
Desc: Tifa's sturdy outer armor protects her from a certain degree of Physical DMG. (Increases Physical Resistance.)

Name: DRes-
Desc: Its unstable consciousness signal makes it prone to corruption. (Reduces Dark Resistance.)

Name: IRes-
Desc: Huaxu's power output relies on a persistent high-temperature environment. The inability to withstand low temperatures is her fatal weakness. (Ice Resistance reduced)

Name: Pres+
Desc: Huaxu has activated her defense protocol that greatly enhances her resistance to physical attacks. (Physical Resistance increased)

Name: Astraphobia
Desc: Gabriel is vulnerable to electric shocks as many of his wires are exposed. Electric attacks can deal more damage to him. (Lightning Resistance reduced)

Name: Fire Proof
Desc: Fire cannot keep burning on Gabriel because of his delicate body structure and flame retardant power cables. (Fire Resistance boosted)

Name: Frail
Desc: Cannot resist physical impacts after the structure is weakened. Physical DMG received is increased significantly.

Name: Combustible
Desc: Easily ignited by high temperatures and causes huge explosions. Fire DMG received is increased significantly.

Name: Frost
Desc: The phenomenon of freezing expansion will occur at low temperatures. Ice DMG received is increased significantly.

Name: Electrode
Desc: Electric shocks will overload the circuits and thus cause paralysis. Lightning DMG received is increased significantly.

Name: Corrosion
Desc: The internal structure has been corroded by excessively stored radiant energy. Dark DMG received is increased significantly.

Name: Play Cute
Desc: Shark-speare thinks she is too strong for you. All she needs to do is play cute and go easy on you.

Name: Injured
Desc: Due to past experience and the demand for camouflage, Lamia's defense ability is also her fatal flaw. While camouflaged, Lamia will take increased DMG from Basic Attacks and Signature Moves.

Name: Silence
Desc: 3-Ping Basic Skill Attacks can impact Hamlet's internal program and based on this feature, increase all DMG taken by 15% every after Hamlet receives a 3-Ping Basic Skill Attack. Stacks up to 8 times.

Name: Super Cute
Desc: Shark-speare is SUPER cute!

Name: Steel-willed
Desc: Fight with all your might and passion is the the greatest respect for your enemy.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Power</size></color>
Desc: α will show off her new "Power".

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>The True Power</size></color>
Desc: α will unleash her "ultimate Power" at the critical moment.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Precise Planning - β</size></color>
Desc: Switch cooldown increases by 2s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Precise Planning - β</size></color>
Desc: Switch cooldown increases by 5s.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Precise Planning - β</size></color>
Desc: Switch cooldown increases by 10s.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Soul Meltdown I</size></color>
Desc: Your Constructs have a higher chance to be controlled by the threads when attacked.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Soul Meltdown II</size></color>
Desc: Your Constructs have a greatly higher chance to be controlled by the threads when attacked.

Name: The True Power
Desc: α will cast the <color=#FF0000>new battle skill</color> based on the selected Affix. Get ready for the <color=#FF0000>new power</color> from α!
TeachingContents: text: When α's HP drops to 80% and 40% respectively, she will further awaken the power inside her.

Name: Soul Pull
Desc: When attacked by Madorea, your Constructs have a chance to be <color=#FF0000>pulled by threads</color>. Madorea will <color=#FF0000>control your Constructs</color> when they <color=#FF0000>have 3 threads on them</color>.

Name: Pull Break
Desc: After gaining control of your Constructs, Madorea will <color=#34aff9>spend Control Energy</color> and <color=#FF0000>cast Puppet Skills</color> to attack your team. When the Control Energy is used up, your Constructs will be <color=#34aff9>back under your control</color>.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#34aff9>Attack Madorea's back</color> in the Matrix to <color=#34aff9>weaken her Control Energy</color>.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Bloodlust</size></color>
Desc: Enemies gain 15% more DMG for every 20% HP lost.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Shield I</size></color>
Desc: In every 10s, enemies will gain a shield equal to 5% of their current HP (they will immediately get one such shield when they spawn).

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Shield II</size></color>
Desc: In every 10s, enemies will gain a shield equal to 10% of their current HP (they will immediately get one such shield when they spawn).

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Shield III</size></color>
Desc: In every 10s, enemies will gain a shield equal to 15% of their current HP (they will immediately get one such shield when they spawn).

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Closed Loop</size></color>
Desc: Enemies' Extra DMG Reduction increases by 30% when taking DMG farther than 4m

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Closed Loop II</size></color>
Desc: Enemies' Extra DMG Reduction increases by 45% when taking DMG from more than 4m away.

Name: <color=#34aff9><size=34>Closed Loop III</size></color>
Desc: Enemies' Extra DMG Reduction increases by 60% when taking DMG from more than 4m away.

Name: Reboot Prohibited
Desc: Due to Madorea's interference, you <color=#FF0000>cannot restart or revive</color> in this stage.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Strategic Shift</size></color>
Desc: When Dottie is attacked and runs away, she will launch an extra special attack at the character.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Control Freak</size></color>
Desc: When the character's HP drops to 50%, Dottie will try to control them. When the character is under Dottie's control, they will restore Dodge Gauge value slower.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Powerful Minion</size></color>
Desc: Dottie will summon an extra elite enemy for each wave.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Armor Deprivation</size></color>
Desc: Enemy attacks will reduce the character's Resistances.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Twist the Knife</size></color>
Desc: Characters with less than 50% HP will receive Extra DMG.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Twins</size></color>
Desc: Primal Projection will summon its phantom to assist after casting a Signature Move across the screen.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Hyperspace Domination</size></color>
Desc: Matrix has less impact on the Primal Projection. Deceleration and other control effects will lose effect.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Annihilation</size></color>
Desc: Primal Projection's Signature Move across the screen will seckill all characters it hits.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Resistance</size></color>
Desc: One needs to trigger the Matrix 5 times instead of 2 times to convert their phantom.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Flexible Strategy</size></color>
Desc: Reduces character switching cooldown by 3s. Characters switched in gain a 25% DMG bonus for 4s.

Name: Time Phantom
Desc: Upon entering phase 2, the Primal Projection will twist space-time and create your <color=#FF0000>Time Phantom</color>.
TeachingContents: text: <color=#FF0000>Time Phantom</color> will copy most of your actions several seconds ago and <color=#FF0000>deal damage to you</color>.

Name: Distortion Matrix
Desc: Coping Method: <color=#FF0000>Time Phantom</color> can be <color=#34aff9>interfered by the Matrix</color> you triggered. After you have triggered the Matrix a certain times, the Time Phantom will be <color=#34aff9>converted</color>, become one of your members, and deal damage to the enemy.
TeachingContents: text: Time Phantom will not copy some special skills

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Energy Absorption</size></color>
Desc: Killing enemies will restore HP and Signature Move Energy.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Ultimate Boost</size></color>
Desc: Signature Move DMG increases.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Body of Suffering</size></color>
Desc: Each thorn will increase Tifa's Resistances by 12%, up to 48% Resistances in total.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Pillar of Torture</size></color>
Desc: Each thorn will increase Tifa's Extra DMG Bonus by 8%, up to 32% Extra DMG.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Cocoon of Pain</size></color>
Desc: Tifa will restore 2% HP after casting the cocooning skill successfully.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Thorn Spike</size></color>
Desc: Tifa's attacks will also reduce characters' Movement Speed on hit for 5s.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Call for Healing</size></color>
Desc: When healed while casting a QTE, the character will immediately activate another QTE, and the DMG dealt by the character will clear the enemy's Super Armor. The effect lasts for 15s.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Combo Strike</size></color>
Desc: QTE and character switch CD decrease by 1s.

Name: Pillar of Torture
Desc: Some of Tifa's skills will <color=#FF0000>summon thorns</color> that will <color=#FF0000>provide special buffs to the boss</color> based on the entries and Tifa will also <color=#FF0000>cast special skills</color> to attack on the thorns.
TeachingContents: text: When Tifa launches attacks on a thorn, <color=#FF0000>the thorn will defend Tifa</color>, and a Super Armor will appear. <color=#34aff9>If Tifa's Super Armor is cleared</color> when she's casting a skill, <color=#34aff9>the thorn will be removed</color>.

Name: Cocoon of Pain
Desc: <color=#FF0000>When attacked in the Matrix</color>, Tifa will <color=#FF0000>cocoon to defend herself</color>, and a Super Armor will appear.
TeachingContents: text: If you fail to clear the Super Armor bar when Tifa is cocooning, <color=#FF0000>4 thorns will appear on the battlefield</color>.
text:
text: Clearing the Super Armor bar will <color=#34aff9>remove all thorns on the battlefield</color>.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Deadly Grasp</size></color>
Desc: Dodge Gauge will be cleared if the character gets caught by Fu Shen.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Kowloong Trap</size></color>
Desc: Fu Shen gains a shield of 20% Max HP after increasing its Enhancement Level.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Deafening Roar</size></color>
Desc: Fu Shen's laser attacks deal 50% more DMG.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Healing Wave</size></color>
Desc: You restore 20% Max HP after increasing your Enhancement Level.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Agility</size></color>
Desc: Dodge Gauge basic recovery speed increases.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Real-Man Field</size></color>
Desc: Fu Shen takes 45% less DMG from attacks from 4m away.

Name: Dragon Field
Desc: Both Fu Shen and the character will gain <color=#34aff9>special enhancements</color> based on their battle performance.
TeachingContents: Text: Fu Shen gets one <color=#FF0000>Enhancement Level</color> up when performing a <color=#FF0000>Taunt Action</color> or <color=#FF0000>Dragon Roar</color>, up to 2 levels up. Each level will improve Fu Shen's <color=#FF0000>Overall Performance</color>.

Text: The character gains Enhancement Points when <color=#34aff9>dodging and reflecting</color> an attack from Fu Shen. With a certain amount of Enhancement Points, the character will get one <color=#34aff9>Enhancement Level</color> up, up to 3 levels. Each level will <color=#34aff9>greatly improve the character's DMG Piercing and overall frame performance</color>.

Name: Dragon Ravage
Desc: All Fu Shen's skills that can catch the character will deal <color=#FF0000>massive damage</color>. The higher your HP, the more damage Fu Shen will deal.
TeachingContents: Text: If the character gets caught by Fu Shen, they will receive massive damage, get one <color=#FF0000>Enhancement Level</color> down, and lose part of their Enhancement Points. Meanwhile, Fu Shen's <color=#FF0000>Enhancement Level will go up</color>.

Text: If the character <color=#34aff9>dodges or reflects</color> Fu Shen's attack that attempts to catch them, Fu Shen will <color=#FF0000>lose one Enhancement Level</color>, and the character will receive massive <color=#34aff9>Enhancement Points</color>.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Reloading</size></color>
Desc: The character gains 2 random sets of Signal Orbs after casting a Signature.

Name: Green Voiceprint
Desc: In battle, the voiceprint above the character's head will turn <color=#34aff9>green</color> when they <color=#34aff9>dodge, perform a Signature Move</color>, <color=#34aff9>pull away from</color> Nigel and stop moving, or when they are not casting any skill.
TeachingContents: Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFighthongyinbo.png

Name: Yellow Voiceprint
Desc: When the character has not lost their vision completely, the voiceprint will turn yellow <color=#34aff9>right before Nigel launches an attack</color>.
TeachingContents: Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFighthuangyinbo.png

Name: Red Voiceprint
Desc: The voiceprint will turn <color=#34aff9>red</color> when Nigel <color=#34aff9>launches an attack</color>, <color=#34aff9>detects the character</color>, or is <color=#34aff9>too close to the character</color>. The Red Voiceprint will make the character <color=#34aff9>gradually lose vision</color>.
TeachingContents: Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightzhimang.png

Name: Blindness
Desc: The character's <color=#34aff9>visual field decreases gradually</color> when the voiceprint is red. Attacks launched against the enemy in the Blind State <color=#34aff9>can be dodged</color>. Attacks launched when the voiceprint is <color=#34aff9>green</color> <color=#34aff9>cannot be dodged or blocked</color>. Meanwhile, the character <color=#34aff9>recovers visual field slowly</color> when they're not completely blind.
TeachingContents: Assets/Product/Texture/Image/UiBabelTower/BgFightlvyinbo.png

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Rapid Blindness</size></color>
Desc: Loses vision faster.

Name: <color=#CF0000><size=34>Rapid Blindness</size></color>
Desc: Loses vision greatly faster.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Speed of Red</size></color>
Desc: The character restore Dodge Gauge faster under the Red Voiceprint.

Name: <color=#78db64><size=34>Might of Green</size></color>
Desc: The character deals more damage under the Green Voiceprint.
